http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Georgia Performance Standards for Piano supports the National Association for Music Education (MENC) expectation of promoting a comprehensive, balanced, and sequential music education for all students based upon the National Standards for Music Education. Georgia Performance Standards for Piano are arranged in four categories: Skills and Techniques/Performance, Creation, Critical Analysis/Investigate, and Cultural and Historical Context. The standards help organize the curriculum into manageable and related units designed to guide the student through valuable musical experiences.
Beginning Piano
